            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="36" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d36">
                <head>No. 36.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Kasson</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-02-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 18, 1880</date>.
                            (Received March 4.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 295.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: A telegram from Mr. William Paine, the
                        commercial agent of the United States at Bucharest, addressed to me, was
                        yesterday received at this legation, as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Recognition of Roumania by England, France, Germany, takes place
                                Friday next. Have been asked by minister foreign affairs what our
                                government intends doing. Please instruct me.</p>
                        <p rend="right">WILLIAM PAINE.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>To this telegram I have replied as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Await instructions from Washington. Are you yet recognized as
                                consular officer?</p>
                        <p rend="right">KASSON.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JOHN A. KASSON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
